<subSubSection id="63E2800F002C11986F020416BA8C12CF" pageId="null" pageNumber="434" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph id="318A781D72BF463B214D1DC74151CC33" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">Leers Segge</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="863EB848AF220459577710D401FC2B25" pageId="null" pageNumber="434" type="description">
<paragraph id="332594CA919C9F7EEE904728B7EEB4FE" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">
30-100 cm hoch. 
<normalizedToken id="9677E9BEC3C9916A1D1498CBFB5C6206" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
3-5 mm breit, oft so lang wie der Stengel, 
<emphasis id="1651E78D3867F3A46A8D941E153DA730" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">steif aufrecht;</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="B086FEE16BC7E00036A4F3FC109769D4" originalValue="Blatthäutchen" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">Blatthaeutchen</normalizedToken>
so hoch wie breit. 
<emphasis id="AE23E67810B43E44DEF14244329454C0" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">Stengeldurchmesser 1-2 mm.</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="F48BDF7A4EB4596B720C339313E6DE36" originalValue="Blütenstand" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">Bluetenstand</normalizedToken>
bis 7 cm lang, 
<emphasis id="01528F339BEDB32965AC5F2D8F69EE95" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">unterbrochen:</emphasis>
in der untern 
<normalizedToken id="5947FF598A23F0B0F4E694529B087FDF" originalValue="Hälfte" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">Haelfte</normalizedToken>
des 
<normalizedToken id="164E9836938767D6A2C3348AE956BE4B" originalValue="Blütenstandes" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">Bluetenstandes</normalizedToken>
<emphasis id="4B033265114EC829DCD0A8A5E3572A95" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">3-4 entfernt stehende</emphasis>
(Abstand etwa 2-3 cm) 
<emphasis id="2640AFF20B579783E05B3C6D2377FEC2" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">
<normalizedToken id="1BF4E7137D49BE2AD4746B581BA99E80" originalValue="Ährenknäuel" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">Aehrenknaeuel</normalizedToken>
, diese 1-2 cm lang
</emphasis>
, aus 2-5 
<normalizedToken id="DC060AD002F02AA381FBEEAFFA1A2C67" originalValue="Ähren" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">Aehren</normalizedToken>
bestehend. 
<normalizedToken id="8B0B283D9ACEA9A6323DABF2310E75B6" originalValue="Fruchtschläuche" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">Fruchtschlaeuche</normalizedToken>
4-5,5 mm lang, etwa 2,1-2,3mal so lang wie breit, am Grunde mit nur wenig schwammigem Gewebe, braun, 
<normalizedToken id="8422C12753186AF103F9F87E3FBE464E" originalValue="glänzend" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">glaenzend</normalizedToken>
, 
<emphasis id="E63D0760429E4FDD75C385AF7B57DF15" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">sparrig abstehend.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5299BE0024530CF9FC24AF0BA06BB8FF" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">
<emphasis id="8D3F503E49755C0938EED228E67AF757" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">Zytologische Angaben. 2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="23C73FD05B83F82CD09ECE62285FEC19" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">56:</emphasis>
Material aus dem Jura (Born) (Studer in lit.). 
<emphasis id="D9B5A6E19490E213E9C9C89375C8D972" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">2n = 58:</emphasis>
Material aus Schweden (Heilborn 1924Heilborn 1939), aus der Schweiz (Boningen) (Studer in lit.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D2C2C0EA995767719E9D55C0B0BABAE" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">
<emphasis id="B1D571069FCC354CE2093AB33DF3BF36" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">Standort.</emphasis>
Kollin. Trockene bis feuchte, 
<normalizedToken id="D328B6AC2B4BB459E5288FC36764E662" originalValue="durchlässige" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">durchlaessige</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="4A7F2BE702521C27B14C206032EBCB34" originalValue="Böden" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">Boeden</normalizedToken>
. 
<normalizedToken id="D8A81E76C614BA834B9B9F8A06907956" originalValue="Gebüschränder" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">Gebueschraender</normalizedToken>
, oft in lichten 
<normalizedToken id="DDC80F71BEDFA9F7AF0662C0669254E3" originalValue="Laubwäldern" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">Laubwaeldern</normalizedToken>
(nicht fruchtend).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DDD37F59AEFA49F91442163551D802D1" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">
<emphasis id="5AF71FD66C9647B629291814953CD010" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">Verbreitung.</emphasis>
(
<normalizedToken id="429EFB86C8A443B754C16F63FCFFF4AE" originalValue="Ungenügend" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">Ungenuegend</normalizedToken>
bekannt, da oft nicht von 
<taxonomicName id="54FF0E848574B4C9C47BA13D1D0DA88E" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="434" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="divulsa">
<emphasis id="425BBC7EC56C84DC466E7D7521E05F90" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">C. divulsa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
unterschieden). 
<emphasis id="B45D8B87674608D0E3A159D0BD22AB29" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">Eurasiatische Pflanze:</emphasis>
In 
<taxonomicName id="1D398D033A886057C49D1964CA662FD6" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Europa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="null" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Europa</taxonomicName>
bis 59° NB; aus 
<normalizedToken id="F17CE847D446FF7029E5CBDEB993D4E0" originalValue="Großbritannien" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">Grossbritannien</normalizedToken>
nicht angegeben; im Mediterrangebiet selten; Kleinasien, Kaukasus, Persien, Himalaja, Mongolei. - Im Gebiet Verbreitung wie 
<emphasis id="E4BA0CE6114A1F162912A6AE25D7D55A" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="434">C. Pairaei</emphasis>
(Nr. 20b), aber seltener.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
